ttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Ftravel%2Farticle%2F20211208-foula-britains-most-remote-inhabited-island%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroughly%2030%20residents%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20celebrates%20Christmas%2012%20days%20later%20than%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%20on%20January%206.%20The%20difference%20stems%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20Foula%20retained%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nottingham.ac.uk%2Fmanuscriptsandspecialcollections%2Fresearchguidance%2Fdatingdocuments%2Fjuliangregorian.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJulian%20calendar%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20rest%20of%20Great%20Britain%20adopted%20the%20modern%20Gregorian%20calendar%20in%201752.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BQuite%20a%20lot%20of%20households%20here%20on%20the%20island%20really%20don't%20do%20anything%20at%20all%20on%20the%20twenty-fifth%20of%20December%2C%26quot%3B%20resident%20Ken%20Gear%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20main%20game%20is%20indeed%20on%20the%20sixth%20of%20January.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGear%20noted%20that%20residents%20don't%20live%20on%20a%2012-day%20delay%20year-round%2C%20though%20they%20do%20%26quot%3Bcelebrate%20a%20few%20occasions%20by%20the%20old%20calendar.%26quot%3B%20This%20includes%20Christmas%20(or%20%26quot%3BYule%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Gear%20calls%20it)%2C%20New%20Year's%20Day%20(or%20%26quot%3BNewerday%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20falls%20on%20Jan.%2013)%20and%20Halloween%20(%26quot%3BOld%20Hallowmas.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFoula%20is%20located%20roughly%20100%20miles%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20the%20mainland%2C%20and%20is%20accessible%20via%20ferry.%20It%20doesn't%20have%20a%20shop%20or%20a%20pub%20%E2%80%94%20though%20there%20is%20one%20nurse%20and%20one%20teacher%20on%20the%20island%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cntraveler.com%2Fstory%2Fthe-scottish-island-that-celebrates-christmas-12-days-late%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECond%C3%A9%20Nast%20Traveler%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20city%20is%20also%20known%20for%20its%20birdwatching%20tourism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20evidence%20of%20its%20deeply-steeped%20traditions%3F%20Foula%20also%20happens%20to%20be%20the%20last%20place%20in%20Great%20Britain%20where%20the%20ancient%20Norse%20language%20of%20Norn%20was%20spoken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELocals%20'go%20visiting'%20on%20Christmas%2C%20swigging%2C%20singing%20and%20dancing%20into%20the%20night%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225568%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20field%20with%20a%20house%20that%20has%20a%20smoking%20chimney%20in%20the%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658c9e86ab6f2ebb11f74382%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGear%20moved%20back%20to%20Foula%20after%20living%20abroad%20for%20several%20years.%3Cp%3EJeff%20J%20Mitchell%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGear%20grew%20up%20in%20Foula%20and%20says%20his%20ancestry%20on%20the%20island%20dates%20back%20hundreds%20of%20years%20%E2%80%94%20if%20not%20more.%20After%20working%20and%20living%20abroad%2C%20he%20moved%20back%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20their%20two%20kids%20almost%20seven%20years%20ago.%20He%20operates%20an%20inn%20for%20tourists%20on%20the%20island%2C%20and%20also%20works%20as%20an%20engineer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20suppose%20it's%20that%20time%20of%20year%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20when%20reached%20by%20a%20reporter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGear%20said%20that%20residents%20tend%20to%20spend%20the%20holiday%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Christmas%2C%20Gear%20said%20locals%20%26quot%3Bgo%20visiting%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20whereby%20one%20resident%20offers%20or%20is%20chosen%20to%20serve%20as%20the%20de%20facto%20host.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThere'll%20be%20one%20household%20that's%20maybe%20agreed%20%E2%80%94%20or%20maybe%20they%20haven't%20really%20agreed%20%E2%80%94%20but%20everyone%20will%20eventually%20gravitate%20to%20someone's%20ho