twork's%20expectations%20were%20so%20low%20it%20positioned%20their%20show%20opposite%20the%20top-rated%20%26quot%3BBonanza.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Smothers%20Brothers%20would%20prove%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20television%20history%2C%20with%20its%20sharp%20eye%20for%20pop%20culture%20trends%20and%20young%20rock%20stars%20such%20as%20the%20Who%20and%20Buffalo%20Springfield%2C%20and%20its%20daring%20sketches%20%E2%80%94%20ridiculing%20the%20Establishment%2C%20railing%20against%20the%20Vietnam%20War%2C%20and%20portraying%20members%20of%20the%20era's%20hippie%20counterculture%20as%20gentle%2C%20fun-loving%20spirits%20%E2%80%94%20found%20an%20immediate%20audience%20with%20young%20baby%20boomers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20moderate.%20We%20were%20never%20out%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Dick%20Smothers%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we%20were%20the%20first%20people%20through%20that%20door.%20It%20just%20sort%20of%20crept%20in%20as%20the%20'60s%20crept%20in.%20We%20were%20part%20of%20that%20generation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20show%20reached%20No.%2016%20in%20the%20ratings%20in%20its%20first%20season.%20It%20also%20drew%20the%20ire%20of%20network%20censors.%20After%20years%20of%20battling%20with%20the%20brothers%20over%20the%20show's%20creative%20content%2C%20the%20network%20abruptly%20canceled%20the%20program%20in%201970%2C%20accusing%20the%20siblings%20of%20failing%20to%20submit%20an%20episode%20in%20time%20for%20the%20censors%20to%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%2040%20years%20later%2C%20when%20Smothers%20was%20awarded%20an%20honorary%20Emmy%20for%20his%20work%20on%20the%20show%2C%20he%20jokingly%20thanked%20the%20writers%20he%20said%20had%20gotten%20him%20fired.%20He%20also%20showed%20that%20the%20years%20had%20not%20dulled%20his%20outspokenness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20for%20me%20to%20stay%20silent%20when%20I%20keep%20hearing%20that%20peace%20is%20only%20attainable%20through%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20Smothers%20said%20at%20the%202008%20Emmy%20Awards%20as%20his%20brother%20sat%20in%20the%20audience%2C%20beaming.%20He%20dedicated%20his%20award%20to%20those%20%26quot%3Bwho%20feel%20compelled%20to%20speak%20out%20and%20are%20not%20afraid%20to%20speak%20to%20power%20and%20won't%20shut%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20three%20years%20the%20show%20was%20on%20television%2C%20the%20brothers%20constantly%20battled%20with%20CBS%20censors%20and%20occasionally%20outraged%20viewers%20as%20well%2C%20particularly%20when%20Smothers%20joked%20that%20Easter%20%26quot%3Bis%20when%20Jesus%20comes%20out%20of%20his%20tomb%20and%20if%20he%20sees%20his%20shadow%2C%20he%20goes%20back%20in%20and%20we%20get%20six%20more%20weeks%20of%20winter.%26quot%3B%20At%20Christmas%2C%20when%20other%20hosts%20were%20sending%20best%20wishes%20to%20soldiers%20fighting%20overseas%2C%20Smothers%20offered%20his%20to%20draft%20dodgers%20who%20had%20moved%20to%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20still%20another%20episode%2C%20the%20brothers%20returned%20blacklisted%20folk%20singer%20Pete%20Seeger%20to%20television%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20years.%20He%20performed%20his%20song%20%26quot%3BWaist%20Deep%20in%20the%20Big%20Muddy%2C%26quot%3B%20widely%20viewed%20as%20ridiculing%20President%20Lyndon%20Johnson.%20When%20CBS%20refused%20to%20air%20the%20segment%2C%20the%20brothers%20brought%20Seeger%20back%20for%20another%20episode%20and%20he%20sang%20it%20again.%20This%20time%2C%20it%20made%20the%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20show%20was%20canceled%2C%20the%20brothers%20sued%20CBS%20for%20%2431%20million%20and%20were%20awarded%20%24775%2C000.%20Their%20battles%20with%20the%20network%20were%20chronicled%20in%20the%202002%20documentary%20%26quot%3BSmothered%3A%20The%20Censorship%20Struggles%20of%20the%20Smothers%20Brothers%20Comedy%20Hour.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThomas%20Bolyn%20Smothers%20III%20was%20born%20Feb.%202%2C%201937%2C%20on%20Governors%20Island%2C%20New%20York%2C%20where%20his%20father%2C%20an%20Army%20major%2C%20was%20stationed.%20His%20brother%20was%20born%20two%20years%20later.%20In%201940%20their%20father%20was%20transferred%20to%20the%20Philippines%2C%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20two%20sons%2C%20and%20their%20sister%2C%20Sherry%2C%20accompanied%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Japanese%20bombed%20Pearl%20Harbor%2C%20the%20family%20was%20sent%20home%20and%20Maj.%20Smothers%20remained.%20He%20was%20captured%20by%20the%20Japanese%20during%20the%20war%20and%20died%20in%20captivity.%20The%20family%20eventually%20moved%20to%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20suburb%20of%20Redondo%20Beach%2C%20where%20Smothers%20helped%20his%20mother%20take%20care%20of%20his%20brother%20and%20sister%20while%20she%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTommy%20was%20the%20greatest%20older%20brother.%20He%20took%20care%20of%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Dick%20Smothers%20said.%20%26quot%3BHis%20maturity%20was%20amazing.%20Sometimes%20you%20lose%20part%20of%20your%20childhood.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brothers%20had%20seemed%20unlikely%20to%20make%20television%20history.%20They%20had%20spent%20several%20years%20on%20the%20nightclub%20and%20college%20circuits%20and%20doing%20TV%20guest%20appearances%2C%20honing%20an%20offbeat%20comedy%20routine%20that%20mixed%20folk%20music%20with%20a%20healthy%20dose%20of%20sibling%20rivalry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20would%20come%20on%20stage%2C%20Tom%20with%20a%20guitar%20in%20hand%20and%20Dick%20toting%20an%20upright%20bass.%20They%20would%20quickly%20break%20into%20a%20traditional%20folk%20song%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20%26quot%3BJohn%20Henry%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BPretoria.%26quot%3B%20After%20playing%20several%20bars%2C%20Tom%2C%20positioned%20as%20the%20dumb%20one%20despite%20being%20older%2C%20would%20mess%20up%2C%20then%20quickly%20claim%20he%20had%20meant%20to%20do%20that.%20As%20Dick%2C%20the%20serious%2C%20short-tempered%20one%2C%20berated%20him%20for%20failing%20to%20acknowledge%20his%20error%2C%20he%20would%20scream%20in%20exasperation%2C%20%26quot%3BMom%20always%20liked%20you%20best!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20the%20childlike%20enthusiasm%20through%20ignorance%2C%20and%20me%2C%20the%20teacher%2C%20correcting%20him%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20I'd%20correct%20him%20even%20if%20I%20was%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20Dick%20Smothers%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20the%20perfect%20straight%20man%20for%20my%20brother.%20I%20was%20the%20only%20straight%20man%20for%20my%20brother.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20continued%20that%20shtick%20on%20their%20show%20but%20also%20surrounded%20themselves%20with%20a%20talented%20cast%20of%20newcomers%2C%20both%20writers%20and%20performers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFuture%20actor-filmmaker%20Rob%20Reiner%20was%20among%20those%20on%20the%20crack%20writing%20crew%20the%20brothers%20assembled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTommy%20was%20funny%2C%20smart%2C%20and%20a%20fighter%2C%26quot%3B%20Reiner%20said%20on%20social%20media%20Wednesday.%20%26quot%3BHe%20created%20a%20groundbreaking%20show%20that%20celebrated%20all%20that%20was%20good%20about%20American%20Democracy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20writers%20included%20musician%20Mason%20Williams%20and%20comedian%20Steve%20Martin%2C%20who%20presented%20Smothers%20with%20the%20lifetime%20Emmy.%20Regular%20musical%20guests%20included%20John%20Hartford%2C%20Glen%20Campbell%2C%20and%20Jennifer%20Warnes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brothers%20had%20begun%20their%20own%20act%20when%20Tom%2C%20then%20a%20student%20at%20San%20Jose%20State%20University%2C%20formed%20a%20music%20group%20called%20the%20Casual%20Quintet%20and%20encouraged%20his%20younger%20brother%20to%20learn%20the%20bass%20and%20join.%20The%20brothers%20continued%20on%20as%20a%20duo%20after%20the%20other%20musicians%20dropped%20out%2C%20but%20began%20interspersing%20comedy%20with%20their%20limited%20folk%20music%20repertoire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20never%20wrote%20anything%2C%20we%20just%20made%20it%20up%2C%20and%20tried%20to%20remember%20what%20we%20made%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Dick%20Smothers%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20responded%20to%20Tom%2C%20if%20he%20said%20something%20that%20wasn't%20in%20the%20bit%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20stick%20to%20the%20script%2C%20I%20would%20listen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brothers'%20big%20break%20came%20in%201959%20when%20they%20appeared%20at%20San%20Francisco's%20Purple%20Onion%2C%20then%20a%20hot%20spot%20for%20new%20talent.%20Booked%20for%20two%20weeks%2C%20they%20stayed%20a%20record%2036.%20They%20had%20a%20similar%20run%20at%20New%20York's%20Blue%20Angel.%20But%20to%20their%20disappointment%2C%20they%20couldn't%20get%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Tonight%20Show%2C%26quot%3B%20then%20hosted%20by%20Jack%20Paar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPaar%20kept%20telling%20our%20agent%20he%20didn't%20like%20folk%20singers%20%E2%80%94%20except%20for%20Burl%20Ives%2C%26quot%3B%20Smothers%20told%20the%20AP%20in%201964.%20%26quot%3BBut%20one%20night%20he%20had%20a%20cancellation%2C%20and%20we%20went%20on.%20Everything%20worked%20right%20that%20night.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDick%20Smothers%20said%20Wednesday%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20weren't%20that%20good%20when%20we%20were%20on%20'The%20Tonight%20Show.'%20We%20were%20just%20charmingly%20different.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brothers%20went%20on%20to%20appear%20on%20the%20TV%20shows%20of%20Ed%20Sullivan%2C%20Jack%20Benny%2C%20and%20Judy%20Garland%2C%20among%20others.%20Their%20comedy%20albums%20were%20big%20sellers%20and%20they%20toured%20the%20country%2C%20especially%20colleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20their%20more%20vaunted%20show%2C%20the%20duo%20got%20a%20sitcom%20in%201965.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Smothers%20Brothers%20Show%26quot%3B%20was%20about%20a%20businessman%20(Dick)%20haunted%20by%20his%20late%20brother%20(Tom)%2C%20a%20fledgling%20guardian%20angel.%20It%20lasted%20just%20one%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20CBS%20canceled%20the%20%26quot%3BComedy%20Hour%2C%26quot%3B%20ABC%20picked%20it%20up%20as%20a%20summer%20replacement%2C%20but%20the%20network%20didn't%20bring%20it%20back%20in%20the%20fall.%20NBC%20gave%20them%20a%20show%20in%201975%20but%20it%20failed%20to%20find%20an%20audience%20and%20lasted%20only%20a%20season.%20The%20brothers%20went%20their%20separate%20ways%20for%20a%20time.%20Among%20other%20endeavors%2C%20Smothers%20got%20into%20the%20wine%20business%2C%20launching%20Remick%20Ridge%20Vineyards%20in%20Northern%20California's%20wine%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOriginally%20the%20winery%20was%20called%20Smothers%20Brothers%2C%20but%20I%20changed%20the%20name%20to%20Remick%20Ridge%20because%20when%20people%20heard%20Smothers%20Brothers%20wine%2C%20they%20thought%20something%20like%20Milton%20Berle%20Fine%20Wine%20or%20Larry%2C%20Curly%20and%20Mo%20Vineyards%2C%26quot%3B%20Smothers%20once%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20eventually%20reunited%20to%20star%20in%20the%20musical%20comedy%20%26quot%3BI%20Love%20My%20Wife%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20hit%20that%20ran%20on%20Broadway%20for%20two%20years.%20After%20that%20they%20went%20back%20on%20the%20road%2C%20playing%20casinos%2C%20performing%20arts%20centers%2C%20and%20corporate%20gatherings%20around%20the%20country%2C%20remaining%20popular%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20keep%20resurfacing%2C%26quot%3B%20Smothers%20commented%20in%201997.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20just%20not%20in%20everyone's%20face%20long%20enough%20to%20really%20get%20old.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20successful%2020th%20anniversary%20%26quot%3BSmothers%20Brothers%20Comedy%20Hour%26quot%3B%20in%201988%2C%20CBS%20buried%20the%20hatchet%20and%20brought%20them%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20show%20was%20quickly%20canceled%2C%20though%20it%20stayed%20on%20the%20air%20long%20enough%20for%20Smothers%20to%20introduce%20the%20%26quot%3BYo-Yo%20Man%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20bit%20allowing%20him%20to%20demonstrate%20his%20considerable%20skills%20with%20a%20yo-yo%20while%20he%20and%20his%20brother%20kept%20up%20a%20steady%20patter%20of%20comedy.%20The%20bit%20remained%20in%20their%20act%20for%20yea