lained%20that%20he%20paid%20extra%20because%20he%20has%20a%20medical%20issue%20that%20sometimes%20requires%20%26quot%3Bquick%20access%20to%20the%20bathroom%26quot%3B.%20Because%20of%20this%2C%20he%20wasn't%20willing%20to%20change%20his%20seating%20arranges%2C%20the%20user%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20did%20not%20feel%20it%20was%20fair%20to%20demand%20I%20move%20from%20the%20seat%20I%20planned%20for%20and%20paid%20for%2C%20especially%20since%20she%20apparently%20had%20not%20booked%20an%20aisle%20seat%20herself%20in%20advance%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-embed-height%3D%5C%22316%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FAITAH%2Fcomments%2F18j0r9o%2Faita_for_not_giving_up_my_airline_seat_to_a%2F%5C%22%3EAITA%20for%20not%20giving%20up%20my%20airline%20seat%20to%20a%20pregnant%20woman%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cnby%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fuser%2Fmichaeldonelly%2F%5C%22%3Eu%2Fmichaeldonelly%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FAITAH%2F%5C%22%3EAITAH%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20social%20media%20user%20claimed%20that%20the%20flight%20attendants%20didn't%20try%20to%20help%20resolve%20the%20issue%20and%20there%20weren't%20any%20empty%20aisle%20seats%20that%20could%20facilitate%20the%20pregnant%20woman's%20request.%20He%20concluded%20by%20stating%20that%20his%20family%20backed%20the%20woman%20as%20they%20felt%20that%20he%20should%20have%20%26quot%3Binconvenienced%26quot%3B%20himself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20being%20shared%2C%20the%20Reddit%20post%20has%20accumulated%20more%20than%2015%2C000%20upvotes.%20In%20the%20comments%20section%2C%20users%20praised%20the%20man%20for%20keeping%20his%20seat%20since%20he%20made%20specific%20accommodations%20before%20the%20flight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNTA.%20%5BNot%20the%20a******%5D%20She%20should%20have%20booked%20another%20seat%20she%20wanted%20herself%20or%20not%20gone%20on%20the%20flight.%20Seems%20she%20just%20assumed%20she%20wouldn't%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20it%2C%20since%20some%20sucker%20was%20going%20to%20move.%20The%20flight%20attendants%20are%20at%20fault%20for%20not%20mediating.%20At%20some%20point%20they%20should%20have%20told%20her%20to%20go%20back%20to%20her%20seat%20(and%20all%20of%20this%20is%20regardless%20of%20your%20medical%20issues.%20You%20paid%20for%20the%20seat.%20She%20didn't.)%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20one%20user.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fflight-attendants-reveal-5-dirtiest-rarely-cleaned-spots-on-an-airplane-4751587%5C%22%3EFlight%20Attendants%20Reveal%205%20%26quot%3BDirtiest%2C%20Rarely%20Cleaned%26quot%3B%20Spots%20On%20An%20Airplane%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20she%20felt%20entitled%20to%20it%20because%20she%20was%20pregnant.%20She%20thought%20she%20could%20use%20that%20to%20her%20advantage.%20But%2C%20she%20found%20out%20she%20couldn't.%20And%20rightfully%20so%20OP!!!%20You%20booked%20and%20paid%20for%20that%20seat.%20NTA%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20another.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNTA-%20I%20say%20this%20as%20someone%20who%20has%20been%20pregnant%20and%20has%20flown%20solo%20with%20a%20toddler%20...%20every%20passenger%20has%20equal%20opportunity%20to%20pre-book%20seats%20based%20on%20their%20needs%20and%20preferences.%20It's%20no%20one's%20business%20why%20you%20booked%20that%20seat.%20Was%20the%20passenger%20or%20airline%20going%20to%20reimburse%20you%20for%20the%20cost%20of%20pre-booking%20the%20seat%3F%20Zero%20obligation%20for%20you%20to%20move%2C%26quot%3B%20commented%20a%20third%20user.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703694240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-03%2Fqm26llk_plane-generic-_625x300_26_March_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fman-refusing-to-swap-seats-with-pregn