%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703655783000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F27111147%2F25852973543_bcff837860_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fin-9-charts-indias-growing-debt-problem-has-crisis-like-symptoms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Crisis%E2%80%99%20needs%20to%20be%20viewed%20not%20in%20terms%20of%20present%20debt%20volume%20but%20in%20the%20larger%20trend%20and%20macroeconomic%20connection%20observable%20between%20rising%20government%20debt%20and%20other%20macro%20aggregates.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fin-9-charts-indias-growing-debt-problem-has-crisis-like-symptoms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gujarat%20State%20Police%20Complaint%20Authority%20Accepted%201%20Among%20839%20Complaints%20for%20Probe%20in%202022%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F27104735%2Fimage-1673.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20an%20unusual%20move%2C%20the%20Gujarat%20State%20Police%20Accountability%20Complaints%20Authority%20(SPCA)%20had%20found%20only%20one%20among%20839%20complaints%20it%20had%20received%20during%202022%20within%20its%20jurisdiction%2C%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20replies%20have%20shown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20report%20by%20the%20Commonwealth%20Human%20Rights%20Initiative%20(CHRI)%2C%20which%20collated%20RTI%20replies%20from%20various%20SPCAs%2C%20has%20highlighted%20that%20such%20an%20action%20by%20the%20Gujarat%20SPCA%20was%20%E2%80%9Csurprising%2C%20given%20that%20its%20mandate%20includes%20broad%20terms%20like%20%E2%80%98misuse%20of%20power%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98dereliction%20of%20duty%E2%80%99%20without%20specifying%20actions%20or%20complaints%20to%20be%20covered%20by%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYet%2C%20only%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20complaints%20are%20being%20accepted%20for%20inquiry%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20report%20titled%20%E2%80%98Police%20Complaints%20Authorities%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20Status%20Gaps%20Challenges%E2%80%99.%20It%20underlined%20that%20the%20SPCA%E2%80%99s%20action%20indicates%20%E2%80%9Ca%20restrictive%20approach%E2%80%9D%20towards%20fulfilling%20its%20mandate%20as%20directed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202006%2C%20the%20apex%20court%2C%20in%20order%20to%20inject%20accountability%20into%20police%20forces%2C%20had%20asked%20all%20state%20governments%20to%20set%20up%20police%20complaints%20authorities%2C%20thus%20fulfilling%20a%20longstanding%20recommendation%20for%20police%20reform.%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20directive%20had%20laid%20out%20broad%20standards%20for%20the%20composition%2C%20mandate%20and%20powers%20of%20such%20authorities%2C%20leading%20as%20many%20as%2017%20states%20to%20have%20passed%20new%20police%20Acts%20and%2For%20amendments%20to%20the%20existing%20ones%20to%20implement%20these%20directives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Gujarat%20enacted%20the%20Bombay%20Police%20(Gujarat)%20Amendment%20Act%2C%202007%2C%20it%20set%20up%20a%20state%20police%20complaints%20authority%20only%20in%20July%202013.%20The%20report%20underlines%20that%20in%20a%20significant%20departure%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20the%20amended%20Act%20allowed%20the%20state%20government%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%20control%20over%20the%20selection%20and%20appointment%20process%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20SPCA%20by%20ensuring%20that%20two%20of%20its%20three%20members%20%E2%80%9Care%20serving%20ex-officio%E2%80%9D%3B%20%E2%80%9Cno%20set%20procedure%20for%20the%20selection%20of%20the%20chairperson%E2%80%9D%3B%20and%20that%20there%20is%20no%20transparent%20process%20to%20nominate%20the%20third%20member%2C%20a%20person%20of%20eminence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20complete%20violation%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20order%2C%20the%20Gujarat%20SPCA%20is%20also%20led%20by%20a%20retired%20Indian%20Administrative%20Service%20officer%20(Balwant%20Singh).%20The%202006%20directive%20had%20explicitly%20stated%20that%20it%20should%20be%20headed%20by%20a%20retired%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2Fhigh%20court%20to%20be%20chosen%20by%20the%20state%20government%20from%20a%20panel%20of%20names%20proposed%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20composition%20of%20the%20district%20authorities%20is%20also%20in%20complete%20violation%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20directive%20because%20the%20district%20superintendent%20of%20police%2C%20the%20additional%20district%20magistrate%2C%20two%20members%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20legislative%20assembly%20elected%20from%20the%20concerned%20district%20and%20the%20deputy%20superintendent%20of%20police%20make%20up%20the%20membership%20of%20the%20district%20level%20authority%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CHRI%20report%20deduced%20from%20the%20RTI%20replies%20of%20Gujarat%20SPCA%20that%20even%20the%20mandate%20of%20the%20authority%20%E2%80%9Cis%20also%20unclear%E2%80%9D.%20This%20is%20also%20because%20the%20amended%20Act%20%E2%80%9Cfailed%20to%20define%E2%80%9D%20what%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20misconduct%2C%20dereliction%20of%20duty%2C%20misuse%20of%20powers%E2%80%9D%20are%2C%20leaving%20the%20SPCA%20in%20a%20grey%20area%20as%20to%20which%20complaints%20to%20consider%20it%20to%20be%20within%20its%20jurisdiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%202022%2C%20only%20one%20out%20of%20839%20complaints%20it%20had%20received%20was%20seen%20by%20SPCA%20as%20within%20its%20jurisdiction%2C%20data%20of%20the%20last%20nine%20years%20provided%20by%20the%20authority%20to%20CHRI%20has%20held%20up%20that%20the%20percentage%20of%20complaints%20that%20it%20considered%20to%20be%20within%20its%20purview%20has%20reduced%20drastically.%20%E2%80%9CFrom%2055%25%20in%202014%20to%20less%20than%201%25%20in%202022.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20(Gujarat)%20SPCA%20has%20increasingly%20shunted%20complaints%20out%20of%20its%20jurisdiction%20to%20the%20police%20department%20for%20inquiry%20instead%20of%20looking%20into%20the%20matters%20itself.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20was%20significant%20was%20also%20that%20no%20information%20was%20provided%20about%20the%20types%20of%20complaints%20SPCA%20had%20received%20or%20action%20recommended%20by%20the%20authority%20in%20cases%20which%20it%20inquired.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20recommended%20amending%20the%20state%20police%20Act%20in%20order%20to%20re-establish%20the%20state%20and%20district%20complaints%20authorities%20and%20allocate%20it%20sufficient%20funds%20and%20human%20resources%20and%20also%20expand%20its%20mandate%20to%20be%20able%20to%20follow%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20mandate.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703654374000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F27104735%2Fimage-1673.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgujarat-state-police-complaint-authority-accepted-1-among-839-complaints-for-probe-in-2022-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20recent%20report%20by%20the%20Commonwealth%20Human%20Rights%20Initiative%2C%20which%20collated%20RTI%20replies%20from%20various%20SPCAs%2C%20said%20that%20only%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20complaints%20are%20being%20accepted%20for%20inquiry.%20This%20underlines%20the%20SPCA%E2%80%99s%20'restrictive%20approach'%20towards%20fulfilling%20its%20mandate%20as%20directed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgujarat-state-police-complaint-authority-accepted-1-among-839-complaints-for-probe-in-2022-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Palestinia